In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims October 2015 as National Disability Employment Awareness Month. He highlights the importance of equal access, equal opportunity, and equal respect for individuals with disabilities. The President acknowledges that despite advancements, people with disabilities still face discrimination, limited access to skills training, and low expectations. He emphasizes the need to promote inclusion in the workplace and remove barriers to employment. The Obama administration is working to strengthen protections against disability-based discrimination and expand employment possibilities for people with disabilities. The President also mentions initiatives such as the Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act (WIOA) and the Achieving a Better Life Experience (ABLE) Act, which aim to provide better opportunities and support for individuals with disabilities. President Obama urges Americans to embrace the talents and skills of individuals with disabilities and promote equal employment opportunities for all.